runner

In [1]:
%%writefile runner.sh
#!/bin/bash

N=$1
M=$2
K=$3

nthreads=$4

block_nrows=$5
block_ncols=$6

run_n_times=$7

calculator=$8

# echo '' > measures.csv

for i in $(seq $run_n_times)
{
    echo -en "\r$N: $i/$run_n_times starting..."
    echo -e "$calculator,$N-$M-$K,$block_nrows-$block_ncols,$nthreads,$(./a.out $N $M $K $nthreads $block_nrows $block_ncols)" >> measures.csv
}
echo ''
